        "subject": "LU-2726 lprocfs: don't trust in_interrupt()",
        "message": "LU-2726 lprocfs: don't trust in_interrupt()\n\nDisabling bottom halves is enough to make in_interrupt() return true\neven if current is in process context. So remove the assertion that\ncfs_in_interrupt() return false for non LPROCFS_STATS_FLAG_IRQ_SAFE\ncounters.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I9db0213c585d437a1a3793da3a1bf1379ef6196d\n"
      },
